CatQuest RPG Requirements

Core Game Loop
- Players create an account or log in so their progress can be stored.
- Players can move between the dashboard, shop, and dungeon from the navigation bar.
- Opening the dungeon page starts a battle automatically.
- Battles are turn-based: the player chooses an action first, then the enemy acts if it is still alive.
- Defeating an enemy gives gold and XP, then another enemy appears automatically.
- Fleeing ends the current dungeon run, resets the defeated-enemy count, restores the player to full HP, and starts a fresh battle.
- If the player is defeated, they lose 30% of the gold earned during the current dungeon run.

Player Stats and Progression
- Player progress includes gold, XP, level, equipped weapon, and equipped armour.
- Player max HP is calculated from level using: (level * 15) + 20.
- XP needed for the next level is calculated using: 30 * current level.
- When the player levels up, overflow XP carries over and stamina is fully restored.
- Player attack comes from the equipped sword, or defaults to 2 with no sword equipped.
- Player defence comes from the equipped armour, or defaults to 0 with no armour equipped.
- Critical-hit chance increases with level during dungeon battles.
- The dashboard shows current gold, level, HP, defence, attack, critical-hit chance, inventory, and the gold leaderboard.

Dungeon Actions
- Scratch: basic attack.
- Defend: temporarily increases defence for the next enemy attack and restores a small amount of HP.
- Heal: restores 20% of maximum HP.
- Flee: leaves the current run and begins a new battle with full HP.
- Stagger: special stamina-based attack.
- Players use stamina for special actions. Maximum stamina is 3 + floor(level / 2), and stamina regenerates on turns where stamina was not spent.
- Action buttons can be selected with the keyboard using A and D, then activated with Enter or Space.

Enemy System
- Enemies are loaded from the database.
- The current enemy pool includes Slime, Zombie Cat, Common Dog, Armoured Dog, Dog Sorcerer, and General Scratch.
- Each enemy has a name, description, sprite, entry message, HP, damage, reward, and optional special type.
- Spawned enemies can receive random variants:
  - Normal: standard stats.
  - Tough: more HP and defence, less attack.
  - Quick: less HP and defence, more attack.
- Every tenth spawned enemy is treated as a boss enemy and can occasionally stun the player.

Shop and Equipment
- Players can spend gold in the shop on swords and hats.
- Swords provide attack stats; hats provide defence stats.
- Purchased items are stored in the player's inventory and cannot be bought twice.
- Some items use custom confirmation prompts before purchase.
- Players can inspect shop items to view their description and stats.
- Players can equip owned swords and hats from the dashboard inventory.
- The shop includes a Mystery Box that costs 100 gold:
  - 0.1% chance to award 5000 gold.
  - 20% chance to award nothing.
  - Otherwise awards a weighted random gold amount between 50 and 250.

User Interface
- Dungeon UI shows:
  - Player and enemy sprites.
  - Player and enemy HP bars.
  - Player gold, level, XP, stamina, and enemies defeated.
  - Current status effects.
  - Battle log.
  - Action buttons.
- Shop UI shows:
  - Player avatar and current gold.
  - Sword and hat tabs.
  - Mystery Box offer.
  - Item cards with image, price, inspect details, and purchase state.
- Dashboard UI shows:
  - Player stats.
  - Inventory with equip controls.
  - Top-five gold leaderboard.

Social Features
- Players can use real-time global chat.
- Players can send private whispers using: /w username message
- Chat history is stored and shown again when the page reloads.

Technical Requirements
- Backend uses Flask, Flask-SocketIO, Flask-SQLAlchemy, and SQLite.
- Frontend uses HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript with DOM manipulation.
